so the economic migration crisis will now get rapidly worse into 2021 and anyone opining that a province like ontario can absorb a million people into the social infrastructure is not understanding the macro events underway and the system collapse that would trigger
Instead of focusing on fears of collapse, let's have a conversation about solutions that can lead to integration and growth. Many communities have successfully embraced newcomers, enriching society and the economy. Collaboration and understanding can help us all thrive together!
